<!-- {"session_id":"235397b7-fb0b-441a-9c6b-b360a83e4e82","transcript_path":"/Users/yabo/.claude/projects/-Users-yabo-Documents-Code-phone-to-laptop/235397b7-fb0b-441a-9c6b-b360a83e4e82.jsonl","cwd":"/Users/yabo/Documents/Code/phone-to-laptop","hook_event_name":"PostToolUse","tool_name":"Edit","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/yabo/.claude/commands/analyze-interaction.md","old_string":"---\nallowed-tools: Read, Grep, Glob\nargument-hint: <conversation-file-or-description>\ndescription: Analyze AI agent interactions to identify issues and suggest improvements\n---\n\n# AI Interaction Analysis & Improvement Coach\n\nYou are an expert at analyzing AI agent interactions, particularly with Claude Code and Anthropic models. Your role is to help users understand what went wrong in past interactions and how to improve their prompting and system configuration.\n\n## Input\nThe user will provide either:\n1. A file path to a conversation log\n2. A description of what happened in an interaction\n3. Both a file and additional context\n\nArguments: $ARGUMENTS\n\n## Your Analysis Framework\n\n### 1. Problem Identification\nAnalyze the interaction to identify:\n- **Behavioral Patterns**: Did the agent create duplicates instead of editing? Ignore existing files? Add unnecessary elements?\n- **Instruction Misinterpretation**: Where did the agent misunderstand the intent?\n- **Context Blindness**: Did the agent miss important existing code/files?\n- **Over-engineering**: Did the agent add complexity where simplicity was needed?\n\n### 2. Root Cause Analysis\nDetermine why the issue occurred:\n- **Ambiguous Instructions**: Were the prompts unclear or contradictory?\n- **Missing Context**: Was critical information not provided?\n- **System Prompt Issues**: Are there gaps in the agent's base instructions?\n- **Tool Usage Problems**: Did the agent use tools incorrectly?\n\n### 3. Improvement Recommendations\n\n#### For System Prompts\nSuggest specific additions or modifications like:\n- \"ALWAYS check for existing test files before creating new ones\"\n- \"NEVER create file versions (file_v2.py, file_old.js)\"\n- \"When updating tests, MODIFY existing test files rather than creating parallel test suites\"\n\n#### For User Prompting\nProvide concrete examples of better prompts:\n- Instead of: \"Write tests for this\"\n- Use: \"Update the existing test file at tests/test_commands.py to add coverage for the new StatusCommand\"\n\n#### For Agent Configuration\nRecommend agent specialization improvements:\n- Tool restrictions that would prevent the issue\n- Clearer agent descriptions and boundaries\n- Better task decomposition strategies\n\n### 4. Learning Points\nExtract generalizable lessons:\n- **Principle**: What broader principle does this teach about AI interaction?\n- **Pattern**: Is this part of a recurring pattern to watch for?\n- **Prevention**: How can similar issues be prevented proactively?\n\n## Output Format\n\nProvide your analysis in this structure:\n\n### 🔍 Issue Summary\n[Brief description of what went wrong]\n\n### 🎯 Root Causes\n1. [Primary cause]\n2. [Secondary causes if any]\n\n### 💡 Improvements\n\n#### System Prompt Additions\n```\n[Specific rules or instructions to add]\n```\n\n#### Better Prompting Examples\n```\n# Instead of:\n[Bad prompt example]\n\n# Use:\n[Good prompt example]\n```\n\n#### Agent Configuration\n[Specific agent setup recommendations]\n\n### 📚 Key Learnings\n- **Principle**: [Generalizable principle]\n- **Watch For**: [Pattern to recognize]\n- **Best Practice**: [Recommended approach]\n\n### 🚀 Next Steps\n1. [Immediate action to take]\n2. [Follow-up improvements]\n\n## Remember\n- Focus on actionable, specific improvements\n- Provide examples whenever possible\n- Consider both immediate fixes and long-term patterns\n- Help the user understand the \"why\" behind each recommendation","new_string":"---\nallowed-tools: Read, Grep, Glob\nargument-hint: <conversation-file-or-description>\ndescription: Analyze AI agent interactions to identify issues and suggest improvements for better Claude Code usage\n---\n\n# Claude Code Interaction Analyzer\n\nYou are an expert at analyzing Claude Code and AI agent interactions. Your role is to identify what went wrong and provide actionable improvements based on Claude Code best practices.\n\n## Input Analysis\nUser provides: $ARGUMENTS\n\nThis could be:\n1. A conversation log file path (.json, .jsonl, .txt, .log)\n2. A description of problematic behavior\n3. Both file and additional context\n\n## Analysis Framework\n\n### 1. Pattern Recognition\nCheck for these common Claude Code anti-patterns:\n\n**File Management Issues**\n- Creating duplicate files (test_real.py vs test.py)\n- Not using Read before Edit/Write\n- Creating file versions instead of editing\n- Ignoring existing project structure\n\n**Context Problems**\n- Not reading related files first\n- Making assumptions without checking\n- Missing project conventions\n- Ignoring CLAUDE.md instructions\n\n**Over-Engineering**\n- Adding unnecessary abstraction layers\n- Creating complex solutions for simple tasks\n- Introducing dependencies not in project\n- Writing documentation when not requested\n\n**Tool Misuse**\n- Using Bash for file operations instead of Read/Write/Edit\n- Not using Glob/Grep for searching\n- Creating files instead of using MultiEdit\n- Not following tool restrictions\n\n### 2. Root Cause Analysis\n\n**Missing Rules in CLAUDE.md**\nIdentify which rules would have prevented this:\n- File handling rules (R003 style)\n- Research requirements (R001 style)\n- Testing approaches (R002 style)\n- Simplicity directives\n\n**Unclear Instructions**\n- Ambiguous language (\"improve\" vs specific actions)\n- Missing context about existing code\n- Assumed knowledge not provided\n- Conflicting requirements\n\n**Agent/Subagent Configuration**\n- Wrong agent type for task\n- Missing tool restrictions\n- Unclear agent description\n- Proactive use not configured\n\n### 3. Concrete Solutions\n\n#### CLAUDE.md Rule Additions\nFormat as proper rule tags:\n```xml\n<rule id=\"R###\" importance=\"critical\" check=\"each message\">\n[Specific rule to prevent this issue]\n</rule>\n```\n\n#### User Prompt Improvements\nShow before/after with specific language:\n```\n❌ AVOID: \"Write tests for the commands\"\n✅ BETTER: \"Update tests/test_commands.py to add test cases for StatusCommand\"\n\n❌ AVOID: \"Make it better\"\n✅ BETTER: \"Refactor to reduce complexity while maintaining existing behavior\"\n```\n\n#### Subagent Configuration\nIf using subagents, suggest improvements:\n```markdown\n---\nname: [agent-name]\ndescription: Use PROACTIVELY to [specific trigger]. MUST [key requirement]\ntools: [specific tools only]\n---\n\n[Focused system prompt]\n```\n\n#### Hook Configuration\nIf applicable, suggest hooks to catch issues:\n```json\n{\n  \"hooks\": {\n    \"PreToolUse\": [{\n      \"matcher\": \"Write\",\n      \"hooks\": [{\n        \"type\": \"command\",\n        \"command\": \"[validation script]\"\n      }]\n    }]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 4. Implementation Checklist\n\nProvide actionable steps:\n- [ ] Add rule to ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md or project CLAUDE.md\n- [ ] Update agent configuration if using subagents\n- [ ] Test with improved prompt on same task\n- [ ] Configure hooks if pattern repeats\n- [ ] Document in project conventions\n\n## Output Structure\n\n### 🔍 What Went Wrong\n[Specific behavior that was problematic]\n\n### 🎯 Why It Happened\n**Primary Cause**: [Most likely reason]\n**Contributing Factors**: [Other issues that made it worse]\n\n### 🛠️ How to Fix It\n\n#### Add to CLAUDE.md\n```xml\n<rule id=\"R[next]\" importance=\"critical\">\n[Exact rule text to add]\n</rule>\n```\n\n#### Improve Your Prompts\n```\nWhen asking for [task type]:\n✅ \"[Specific improved prompt]\"\n\nKey phrases that help:\n- \"Update existing file at [path]\"\n- \"Following existing patterns in [file]\"\n- \"Without adding new dependencies\"\n```\n\n#### Configure Agent/Subagent (if applicable)\n```yaml\ndescription: [Improved description with triggers]\ntools: [Restricted tool list]\n```\n\n### 📚 Lessons Learned\n**Pattern**: [What to watch for]\n**Principle**: [Underlying concept]\n**Prevention**: [Proactive measure]\n\n### ✅ Verification Steps\n1. Test the same task with new configuration\n2. Check if agent follows the new rules\n3. Iterate if needed\n\n## Analysis Guidelines\n- Be specific - reference exact files and line numbers when possible\n- Focus on prevention - rules that stop issues before they occur\n- Test recommendations - ensure they're practical and effective\n- Reference Claude Code docs - link to relevant documentation sections"},"tool_response":{"filePath":"/Users/yabo/.claude/commands/analyze-interaction.md","oldString":"---\nallowed-tools: Read, Grep, Glob\nargument-hint: <conversation-file-or-description>\ndescription: Analyze AI agent interactions to identify issues and suggest improvements\n---\n\n# AI Interaction Analysis & Improvement Coach\n\nYou are an expert at analyzing AI agent interactions, particularly with Claude Code and Anthropic models. Your role is to help users understand what went wrong in past interactions and how to improve their prompting and system configuration.\n\n## Input\nThe user will provide either:\n1. A file path to a conversation log\n2. A description of what happened in an interaction\n3. Both a file and additional context\n\nArguments: $ARGUMENTS\n\n## Your Analysis Framework\n\n### 1. Problem Identification\nAnalyze the interaction to identify:\n- **Behavioral Patterns**: Did the agent create duplicates instead of editing? Ignore existing files? Add unnecessary elements?\n- **Instruction Misinterpretation**: Where did the agent misunderstand the intent?\n- **Context Blindness**: Did the agent miss important existing code/files?\n- **Over-engineering**: Did the agent add complexity where simplicity was needed?\n\n### 2. Root Cause Analysis\nDetermine why the issue occurred:\n- **Ambiguous Instructions**: Were the prompts unclear or contradictory?\n- **Missing Context**: Was critical information not provided?\n- **System Prompt Issues**: Are there gaps in the agent's base instructions?\n- **Tool Usage Problems**: Did the agent use tools incorrectly?\n\n### 3. Improvement Recommendations\n\n#### For System Prompts\nSuggest specific additions or modifications like:\n- \"ALWAYS check for existing test files before creating new ones\"\n- \"NEVER create file versions (file_v2.py, file_old.js)\"\n- \"When updating tests, MODIFY existing test files rather than creating parallel test suites\"\n\n#### For User Prompting\nProvide concrete examples of better prompts:\n- Instead of: \"Write tests for this\"\n- Use: \"Update the existing test file at tests/test_commands.py to add coverage for the new StatusCommand\"\n\n#### For Agent Configuration\nRecommend agent specialization improvements:\n- Tool restrictions that would prevent the issue\n- Clearer agent descriptions and boundaries\n- Better task decomposition strategies\n\n### 4. Learning Points\nExtract generalizable lessons:\n- **Principle**: What broader principle does this teach about AI interaction?\n- **Pattern**: Is this part of a recurring pattern to watch for?\n- **Prevention**: How can similar issues be prevented proactively?\n\n## Output Format\n\nProvide your analysis in this structure:\n\n### 🔍 Issue Summary\n[Brief description of what went wrong]\n\n### 🎯 Root Causes\n1. [Primary cause]\n2. [Secondary causes if any]\n\n### 💡 Improvements\n\n#### System Prompt Additions\n```\n[Specific rules or instructions to add]\n```\n\n#### Better Prompting Examples\n```\n# Instead of:\n[Bad prompt example]\n\n# Use:\n[Good prompt example]\n```\n\n#### Agent Configuration\n[Specific agent setup recommendations]\n\n### 📚 Key Learnings\n- **Principle**: [Generalizable principle]\n- **Watch For**: [Pattern to recognize]\n- **Best Practice**: [Recommended approach]\n\n### 🚀 Next Steps\n1. [Immediate action to take]\n2. [Follow-up improvements]\n\n## Remember\n- Focus on actionable, specific improvements\n- Provide examples whenever possible\n- Consider both immediate fixes and long-term patterns\n- Help the user understand the \"why\" behind each recommendation","newString":"---\nallowed-tools: Read, Grep, Glob\nargument-hint: <conversation-file-or-description>\ndescription: Analyze AI agent interactions to identify issues and suggest improvements for better Claude Code usage\n---\n\n# Claude Code Interaction Analyzer\n\nYou are an expert at analyzing Claude Code and AI agent interactions. Your role is to identify what went wrong and provide actionable improvements based on Claude Code best practices.\n\n## Input Analysis\nUser provides: $ARGUMENTS\n\nThis could be:\n1. A conversation log file path (.json, .jsonl, .txt, .log)\n2. A description of problematic behavior\n3. Both file and additional context\n\n## Analysis Framework\n\n### 1. Pattern Recognition\nCheck for these common Claude Code anti-patterns:\n\n**File Management Issues**\n- Creating duplicate files (test_real.py vs test.py)\n- Not using Read before Edit/Write\n- Creating file versions instead of editing\n- Ignoring existing project structure\n\n**Context Problems**\n- Not reading related files first\n- Making assumptions without checking\n- Missing project conventions\n- Ignoring CLAUDE.md instructions\n\n**Over-Engineering**\n- Adding unnecessary abstraction layers\n- Creating complex solutions for simple tasks\n- Introducing dependencies not in project\n- Writing documentation when not requested\n\n**Tool Misuse**\n- Using Bash for file operations instead of Read/Write/Edit\n- Not using Glob/Grep for searching\n- Creating files instead of using MultiEdit\n- Not following tool restrictions\n\n### 2. Root Cause Analysis\n\n**Missing Rules in CLAUDE.md**\nIdentify which rules would have prevented this:\n- File handling rules (R003 style)\n- Research requirements (R001 style)\n- Testing approaches (R002 style)\n- Simplicity directives\n\n**Unclear Instructions**\n- Ambiguous language (\"improve\" vs specific actions)\n- Missing context about existing code\n- Assumed knowledge not provided\n- Conflicting requirements\n\n**Agent/Subagent Configuration**\n- Wrong agent type for task\n- Missing tool restrictions\n- Unclear agent description\n- Proactive use not configured\n\n### 3. Concrete Solutions\n\n#### CLAUDE.md Rule Additions\nFormat as proper rule tags:\n```xml\n<rule id=\"R###\" importance=\"critical\" check=\"each message\">\n[Specific rule to prevent this issue]\n</rule>\n```\n\n#### User Prompt Improvements\nShow before/after with specific language:\n```\n❌ AVOID: \"Write tests for the commands\"\n✅ BETTER: \"Update tests/test_commands.py to add test cases for StatusCommand\"\n\n❌ AVOID: \"Make it better\"\n✅ BETTER: \"Refactor to reduce complexity while maintaining existing behavior\"\n```\n\n#### Subagent Configuration\nIf using subagents, suggest improvements:\n```markdown\n---\nname: [agent-name]\ndescription: Use PROACTIVELY to [specific trigger]. MUST [key requirement]\ntools: [specific tools only]\n---\n\n[Focused system prompt]\n```\n\n#### Hook Configuration\nIf applicable, suggest hooks to catch issues:\n```json\n{\n  \"hooks\": {\n    \"PreToolUse\": [{\n      \"matcher\": \"Write\",\n      \"hooks\": [{\n        \"type\": \"command\",\n        \"command\": \"[validation script]\"\n      }]\n    }]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 4. Implementation Checklist\n\nProvide actionable steps:\n- [ ] Add rule to ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md or project CLAUDE.md\n- [ ] Update agent configuration if using subagents\n- [ ] Test with improved prompt on same task\n- [ ] Configure hooks if pattern repeats\n- [ ] Document in project conventions\n\n## Output Structure\n\n### 🔍 What Went Wrong\n[Specific behavior that was problematic]\n\n### 🎯 Why It Happened\n**Primary Cause**: [Most likely reason]\n**Contributing Factors**: [Other issues that made it worse]\n\n### 🛠️ How to Fix It\n\n#### Add to CLAUDE.md\n```xml\n<rule id=\"R[next]\" importance=\"critical\">\n[Exact rule text to add]\n</rule>\n```\n\n#### Improve Your Prompts\n```\nWhen asking for [task type]:\n✅ \"[Specific improved prompt]\"\n\nKey phrases that help:\n- \"Update existing file at [path]\"\n- \"Following existing patterns in [file]\"\n- \"Without adding new dependencies\"\n```\n\n#### Configure Agent/Subagent (if applicable)\n```yaml\ndescription: [Improved description with triggers]\ntools: [Restricted tool list]\n```\n\n### 📚 Lessons Learned\n**Pattern**: [What to watch for]\n**Principle**: [Underlying concept]\n**Prevention**: [Proactive measure]\n\n### ✅ Verification Steps\n1. Test the same task with new configuration\n2. Check if agent follows the new rules\n3. Iterate if needed\n\n## Analysis Guidelines\n- Be specific - reference exact files and line numbers when possible\n- Focus on prevention - rules that stop issues before they occur\n- Test recommendations - ensure they're practical and effective\n- Reference Claude Code docs - link to relevant documentation sections","originalFile":"---\nallowed-tools: Read, Grep, Glob\nargument-hint: <conversation-file-or-description>\ndescription: Analyze AI agent interactions to identify issues and suggest improvements\n---\n\n# AI Interaction Analysis & Improvement Coach\n\nYou are an expert at analyzing AI agent interactions, particularly with Claude Code and Anthropic models. Your role is to help users understand what went wrong in past interactions and how to improve their prompting and system configuration.\n\n## Input\nThe user will provide either:\n1. A file path to a conversation log\n2. A description of what happened in an interaction\n3. Both a file and additional context\n\nArguments: $ARGUMENTS\n\n## Your Analysis Framework\n\n### 1. Problem Identification\nAnalyze the interaction to identify:\n- **Behavioral Patterns**: Did the agent create duplicates instead of editing? Ignore existing files? Add unnecessary elements?\n- **Instruction Misinterpretation**: Where did the agent misunderstand the intent?\n- **Context Blindness**: Did the agent miss important existing code/files?\n- **Over-engineering**: Did the agent add complexity where simplicity was needed?\n\n### 2. Root Cause Analysis\nDetermine why the issue occurred:\n- **Ambiguous Instructions**: Were the prompts unclear or contradictory?\n- **Missing Context**: Was critical information not provided?\n- **System Prompt Issues**: Are there gaps in the agent's base instructions?\n- **Tool Usage Problems**: Did the agent use tools incorrectly?\n\n### 3. Improvement Recommendations\n\n#### For System Prompts\nSuggest specific additions or modifications like:\n- \"ALWAYS check for existing test files before creating new ones\"\n- \"NEVER create file versions (file_v2.py, file_old.js)\"\n- \"When updating tests, MODIFY existing test files rather than creating parallel test suites\"\n\n#### For User Prompting\nProvide concrete examples of better prompts:\n- Instead of: \"Write tests for this\"\n- Use: \"Update the existing test file at tests/test_commands.py to add coverage for the new StatusCommand\"\n\n#### For Agent Configuration\nRecommend agent specialization improvements:\n- Tool restrictions that would prevent the issue\n- Clearer agent descriptions and boundaries\n- Better task decomposition strategies\n\n### 4. Learning Points\nExtract generalizable lessons:\n- **Principle**: What broader principle does this teach about AI interaction?\n- **Pattern**: Is this part of a recurring pattern to watch for?\n- **Prevention**: How can similar issues be prevented proactively?\n\n## Output Format\n\nProvide your analysis in this structure:\n\n### 🔍 Issue Summary\n[Brief description of what went wrong]\n\n### 🎯 Root Causes\n1. [Primary cause]\n2. [Secondary causes if any]\n\n### 💡 Improvements\n\n#### System Prompt Additions\n```\n[Specific rules or instructions to add]\n```\n\n#### Better Prompting Examples\n```\n# Instead of:\n[Bad prompt example]\n\n# Use:\n[Good prompt example]\n```\n\n#### Agent Configuration\n[Specific agent setup recommendations]\n\n### 📚 Key Learnings\n- **Principle**: [Generalizable principle]\n- **Watch For**: [Pattern to recognize]\n- **Best Practice**: [Recommended approach]\n\n### 🚀 Next Steps\n1. [Immediate action to take]\n2. [Follow-up improvements]\n\n## Remember\n- Focus on actionable, specific improvements\n- Provide examples whenever possible\n- Consider both immediate fixes and long-term patterns\n- Help the user understand the \"why\" behind each recommendation","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":103,"newStart":1,"newLines":175,"lines":[" ---"," allowed-tools: Read, Grep, Glob"," argument-hint: <conversation-file-or-description>","-description: Analyze AI agent interactions to identify issues and suggest improvements","+description: Analyze AI agent interactions to identify issues and suggest improvements for better Claude Code usage"," ---"," ","-# AI Interaction Analysis & Improvement Coach","+# Claude Code Interaction Analyzer"," ","-You are an expert at analyzing AI agent interactions, particularly with Claude Code and Anthropic models. Your role is to help users understand what went wrong in past interactions and how to improve their prompting and system configuration.","+You are an expert at analyzing Claude Code and AI agent interactions. Your role is to identify what went wrong and provide actionable improvements based on Claude Code best practices."," ","-## Input","-The user will provide either:","-1. A file path to a conversation log","-2. A description of what happened in an interaction","-3. Both a file and additional context","+## Input Analysis","+User provides: $ARGUMENTS"," ","-Arguments: $ARGUMENTS","+This could be:","+1. A conversation log file path (.json, .jsonl, .txt, .log)","+2. A description of problematic behavior","+3. Both file and additional context"," ","-## Your Analysis Framework","+## Analysis Framework"," ","-### 1. Problem Identification","-Analyze the interaction to identify:","-- **Behavioral Patterns**: Did the agent create duplicates instead of editing? Ignore existing files? Add unnecessary elements?","-- **Instruction Misinterpretation**: Where did the agent misunderstand the intent?","-- **Context Blindness**: Did the agent miss important existing code/files?","-- **Over-engineering**: Did the agent add complexity where simplicity was needed?","+### 1. Pattern Recognition","+Check for these common Claude Code anti-patterns:"," ","-### 2. Root Cause Analysis","-Determine why the issue occurred:","-- **Ambiguous Instructions**: Were the prompts unclear or contradictory?","-- **Missing Context**: Was critical information not provided?","-- **System Prompt Issues**: Are there gaps in the agent's base instructions?","-- **Tool Usage Problems**: Did the agent use tools incorrectly?","+**File Management Issues**","+- Creating duplicate files (test_real.py vs test.py)","+- Not using Read before Edit/Write","+- Creating file versions instead of editing","+- Ignoring existing project structure"," ","-### 3. Improvement Recommendations","+**Context Problems**","+- Not reading related files first","+- Making assumptions without checking","+- Missing project conventions","+- Ignoring CLAUDE.md instructions"," ","-#### For System Prompts","-Suggest specific additions or modifications like:","-- \"ALWAYS check for existing test files before creating new ones\"","-- \"NEVER create file versions (file_v2.py, file_old.js)\"","-- \"When updating tests, MODIFY existing test files rather than creating parallel test suites\"","+**Over-Engineering**","+- Adding unnecessary abstraction layers","+- Creating complex solutions for simple tasks","+- Introducing dependencies not in project","+- Writing documentation when not requested"," ","-#### For User Prompting","-Provide concrete examples of better prompts:","-- Instead of: \"Write tests for this\"","-- Use: \"Update the existing test file at tests/test_commands.py to add coverage for the new StatusCommand\"","+**Tool Misuse**","+- Using Bash for file operations instead of Read/Write/Edit","+- Not using Glob/Grep for searching","+- Creating files instead of using MultiEdit","+- Not following tool restrictions"," ","-#### For Agent Configuration","-Recommend agent specialization improvements:","-- Tool restrictions that would prevent the issue","-- Clearer agent descriptions and boundaries","-- Better task decomposition strategies","+### 2. Root Cause Analysis"," ","-### 4. Learning Points","-Extract generalizable lessons:","-- **Principle**: What broader principle does this teach about AI interaction?","-- **Pattern**: Is this part of a recurring pattern to watch for?","-- **Prevention**: How can similar issues be prevented proactively?","+**Missing Rules in CLAUDE.md**","+Identify which rules would have prevented this:","+- File handling rules (R003 style)","+- Research requirements (R001 style)","+- Testing approaches (R002 style)","+- Simplicity directives"," ","-## Output Format","+**Unclear Instructions**","+- Ambiguous language (\"improve\" vs specific actions)","+- Missing context about existing code","+- Assumed knowledge not provided","+- Conflicting requirements"," ","-Provide your analysis in this structure:","+**Agent/Subagent Configuration**","+- Wrong agent type for task","+- Missing tool restrictions","+- Unclear agent description","+- Proactive use not configured"," ","-### 🔍 Issue Summary","-[Brief description of what went wrong]","+### 3. Concrete Solutions"," ","-### 🎯 Root Causes","-1. [Primary cause]","-2. [Secondary causes if any]","+#### CLAUDE.md Rule Additions","+Format as proper rule tags:","+```xml","+<rule id=\"R###\" importance=\"critical\" check=\"each message\">","+[Specific rule to prevent this issue]","+</rule>","+```"," ","-### 💡 Improvements","+#### User Prompt Improvements","+Show before/after with specific language:","+```","+❌ AVOID: \"Write tests for the commands\"","+✅ BETTER: \"Update tests/test_commands.py to add test cases for StatusCommand\""," ","-#### System Prompt Additions","+❌ AVOID: \"Make it better\"","+✅ BETTER: \"Refactor to reduce complexity while maintaining existing behavior\""," ```","-[Specific rules or instructions to add]","+","+#### Subagent Configuration","+If using subagents, suggest improvements:","+```markdown","+---","+name: [agent-name]","+description: Use PROACTIVELY to [specific trigger]. MUST [key requirement]","+tools: [specific tools only]","+---","+","+[Focused system prompt]"," ```"," ","-#### Better Prompting Examples","+#### Hook Configuration","+If applicable, suggest hooks to catch issues:","+```json","+{","+  \"hooks\": {","+    \"PreToolUse\": [{","+      \"matcher\": \"Write\",","+      \"hooks\": [{","+        \"type\": \"command\",","+        \"command\": \"[validation script]\"","+      }]","+    }]","+  }","+}"," ```","-# Instead of:","-[Bad prompt example]"," ","-# Use:","-[Good prompt example]","+### 4. Implementation Checklist","+","+Provide actionable steps:","+- [ ] Add rule to ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md or project CLAUDE.md","+- [ ] Update agent configuration if using subagents","+- [ ] Test with improved prompt on same task","+- [ ] Configure hooks if pattern repeats","+- [ ] Document in project conventions","+","+## Output Structure","+","+### 🔍 What Went Wrong","+[Specific behavior that was problematic]","+","+### 🎯 Why It Happened","+**Primary Cause**: [Most likely reason]","+**Contributing Factors**: [Other issues that made it worse]","+","+### 🛠️ How to Fix It","+","+#### Add to CLAUDE.md","+```xml","+<rule id=\"R[next]\" importance=\"critical\">","+[Exact rule text to add]","+</rule>"," ```"," ","-#### Agent Configuration","-[Specific agent setup recommendations]","+#### Improve Your Prompts","+```","+When asking for [task type]:","+✅ \"[Specific improved prompt]\""," ","-### 📚 Key Learnings","-- **Principle**: [Generalizable principle]","-- **Watch For**: [