<!-- {"session_id":"235397b7-fb0b-441a-9c6b-b360a83e4e82","transcript_path":"/Users/yabo/.claude/projects/-Users-yabo-Documents-Code-phone-to-laptop/235397b7-fb0b-441a-9c6b-b360a83e4e82.jsonl","cwd":"/Users/yabo/Documents/Code/phone-to-laptop","hook_event_name":"PostToolUse","tool_name":"Edit","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/yabo/Documents/Code/phone-to-laptop/tests/verify_analyze_command.md","old_string":"# How to Test /analyze-interaction Command\n\n## Testing Strategy (Per R002)\n\n### 1. How Claude Can Test (Automated)\nCannot directly invoke slash commands from tools, but can verify:\n- Command file exists and is valid markdown\n- Frontmatter is properly formatted\n- Command will be recognized by Claude Code\n\n### 2. How Human Can Test (Manual)\n\n#### Quick Smoke Test\n```\n1. In Claude Code session, type:\n   /analyze-interaction tests/sample_bad_interaction.txt\n\n2. Verify output contains:\n   - Issue Summary mentioning file duplication\n   - Root Cause about missing file checks\n   - System prompt suggestion like \"ALWAYS check for existing test files\"\n   - Better prompting example\n```\n\n#### Real Test with Your Case\n```\n1. Get your actual conversation log where python-test-auditor misbehaved\n2. Run: /analyze-interaction [path-to-that-conversation]\n3. Check if suggestions would have prevented the issue\n```\n\n## Verification Checklist\n- [ ] Command appears in `/help` list\n- [ ] Command accepts file paths as arguments\n- [ ] Command accepts text descriptions\n- [ ] Output identifies the core problem\n- [ ] Suggestions are specific and actionable\n- [ ] System prompt additions are clear rules\n- [ ] Better prompt examples show improvement\n\n## Expected Behavior\nWhen given the sample_bad_interaction.txt, should produce:\n1. Recognition that agent created new files instead of editing\n2. Suggestion to add explicit file-checking rules\n3. Better prompt: \"Update the existing test file at test_commands.py\"\n4. System rule: \"NEVER create file versions (test_real.py, test_v2.py)\"","new_string":"# How to Test /analyze-interaction Command\n\n## Testing Strategy (Per R002)\n\n### 1. How Claude Can Test (Automated)\nCannot directly invoke slash commands from tools, but can verify:\n- Command file exists at ~/.claude/commands/analyze-interaction.md\n- Frontmatter is properly formatted YAML\n- Command will be recognized by Claude Code\n\n### 2. How Human Can Test (Manual)\n\n#### Test Case 1: Python Test Auditor Issue\n```bash\n# In Claude Code session:\n/analyze-interaction tests/sample_bad_interaction.txt\n```\n\n**Expected Output Should Include:**\n\n🔍 **What Went Wrong**: Agent created test_commands_real.py instead of updating test_commands.py\n\n🎯 **Why It Happened**: \n- Primary: No explicit rule against creating file versions\n- Contributing: Agent name implied creating \"real\" tests as separate entity\n\n🛠️ **How to Fix It**:\n```xml\n<rule id=\"R003\" importance=\"critical\">\nNEVER create file versions (index_new.py, script_v2.js, test_real.py)\nYOU MUST edit original files directly\nWhen asked to improve tests, UPDATE existing test files\n</rule>\n```\n\n**Better Prompt Examples**:\n```\n✅ \"Update tests/test_commands.py to replace mocks with real service calls\"\n```\n\n**Subagent Configuration**:\n```yaml\nname: python-test-auditor\ndescription: Reviews and UPDATES EXISTING test files to ensure meaningful testing\ntools: Read, Edit, MultiEdit, Grep\n```\n\n#### Test Case 2: Description Only\n```bash\n/analyze-interaction Agent kept creating new files even after I said to edit existing ones\n```\n\nShould analyze the pattern and suggest prevention strategies.\n\n#### Test Case 3: Real Conversation Log\n```bash\n# If you have an actual .jsonl conversation file:\n/analyze-interaction ~/.claude/projects/[project]/[session].jsonl\n```\n\n## Verification Checklist\n- [ ] Command appears in `/help` list showing \"(user)\"\n- [ ] Accepts file paths (.txt, .log, .json, .jsonl)\n- [ ] Accepts text descriptions\n- [ ] Identifies specific anti-patterns (file duplication, mock overuse, etc.)\n- [ ] Provides CLAUDE.md rule in proper XML format\n- [ ] Shows before/after prompt examples with ❌ and ✅\n- [ ] Suggests subagent configuration if applicable\n- [ ] Includes actionable implementation checklist\n- [ ] References Claude Code documentation patterns\n\n## Success Criteria\nThe command successfully helps when it:\n1. Correctly identifies the root cause (not just symptoms)\n2. Provides a rule that would have prevented the issue\n3. Gives specific prompt language that avoids ambiguity\n4. Suggests configuration changes that enforce better behavior\n5. Teaches a principle that applies to similar situations"},"tool_response":{"filePath":"/Users/yabo/Documents/Code/phone-to-laptop/tests/verify_analyze_command.md","oldString":"# How to Test /analyze-interaction Command\n\n## Testing Strategy (Per R002)\n\n### 1. How Claude Can Test (Automated)\nCannot directly invoke slash commands from tools, but can verify:\n- Command file exists and is valid markdown\n- Frontmatter is properly formatted\n- Command will be recognized by Claude Code\n\n### 2. How Human Can Test (Manual)\n\n#### Quick Smoke Test\n```\n1. In Claude Code session, type:\n   /analyze-interaction tests/sample_bad_interaction.txt\n\n2. Verify output contains:\n   - Issue Summary mentioning file duplication\n   - Root Cause about missing file checks\n   - System prompt suggestion like \"ALWAYS check for existing test files\"\n   - Better prompting example\n```\n\n#### Real Test with Your Case\n```\n1. Get your actual conversation log where python-test-auditor misbehaved\n2. Run: /analyze-interaction [path-to-that-conversation]\n3. Check if suggestions would have prevented the issue\n```\n\n## Verification Checklist\n- [ ] Command appears in `/help` list\n- [ ] Command accepts file paths as arguments\n- [ ] Command accepts text descriptions\n- [ ] Output identifies the core problem\n- [ ] Suggestions are specific and 