<!-- {"session_id":"235397b7-fb0b-441a-9c6b-b360a83e4e82","transcript_path":"/Users/yabo/.claude/projects/-Users-yabo-Documents-Code-phone-to-laptop/235397b7-fb0b-441a-9c6b-b360a83e4e82.jsonl","cwd":"/Users/yabo/Documents/Code/phone-to-laptop","hook_event_name":"PostToolUse","tool_name":"MultiEdit","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/yabo/Documents/Code/phone-to-laptop/tests/verify_analyze_command.md","edits":[{"old_string":"#### Test Case 1: Python Test Auditor Issue\n```bash\n# In Claude Code session:\n/analyze-interaction tests/sample_bad_interaction.txt\n```\n\n**Expected Output Should Include:**\n\n🔍 **What Went Wrong**: Agent created test_commands_real.py instead of updating test_commands.py\n\n🎯 **Why It Happened**: \n- Primary: No explicit rule against creating file versions\n- Contributing: Agent name implied creating \"real\" tests as separate entity\n\n🛠️ **How to Fix It**:\n```xml\n<rule id=\"R003\" importance=\"critical\">\nNEVER create file versions (index_new.py, script_v2.js, test_real.py)\nYOU MUST edit original files directly\nWhen asked to improve tests, UPDATE existing test files\n</rule>\n```\n\n**Better Prompt Examples**:\n```\n✅ \"Update tests/test_commands.py to replace mocks with real service calls\"\n```\n\n**Subagent Configuration**:\n```yaml\nname: python-test-auditor\ndescription: Reviews and UPDATES EXISTING test files to ensure meaningful testing\ntools: Read, Edit, MultiEdit, Grep\n```","new_string":"#### Test Case 1: File Duplication Pattern\n```bash\n# In Claude Code session:\n/analyze-interaction tests/sample_bad_interaction.txt\n```\n\n**Expected Output Should Include:**\n\n⚠️ **Specificity Check**: The example appears to involve test files. Should this solution be generic or specific to testing?\n\n🔍 **What Went Wrong**: Agent created new file with suffix instead of updating existing file\n\n🎯 **Why It Happened**: \n- Primary: No explicit rule against creating file versions\n- Contributing: Ambiguous instruction about \"improving\" vs \"updating\"\n\n🛠️ **How to Fix It**:\n```xml\n<rule id=\"R###\" importance=\"critical\">\nNEVER create file versions with suffixes (_new, _v2, _improved, _real, etc.)\nYOU MUST edit original files directly\nExamples: test.py not test_v2.py, index.js not index_new.js, config.yaml not config_updated.yaml\n</rule>\n```\n\n**Better Prompt Examples (Generic)**:\n```\n❌ AVOID: \"Improve the [files]\"\n✅ BETTER: \"Update [specific_file] to [specific_change]\"\n\nDomain Examples:\n- Web: \"Update components/Button.tsx to use new design system\"\n- API: \"Update routes/auth.py to add rate limiting\"\n- Tests: \"Update test_module.py to replace mocks with real calls\"\n```"},{"old_string":"#### Test Case 2: Description Only\n```bash\n/analyze-interaction Agent kept creating new files even after I said to edit existing ones\n```\n\nShould analyze the pattern and suggest prevention strategies.","new_string":"#### Test Case 2: Description Only\n```bash\n/analyze-interaction Agent kept creating new files even after I said to edit existing ones\n```\n\n**Expected Output Should Include:**\n- Recognition that this is a generic file management issue\n- Request for clarification: \"What types of files? In what context?\"\n- Generic rule that applies to all file types\n- Multiple examples from different domains"},{"old_string":"## Success Criteria\nThe command successfully helps when it:\n1. Correctly identifies the root cause (not just symptoms)\n2. Provides a rule that would have prevented the issue\n3. Gives specific prompt language that avoids ambiguity\n4. Suggests configuration changes that enforce better behavior\n5. Teaches a principle that applies to similar situations","new_string":"## Success Criteria\nThe command successfully helps when it:\n1. Detects when examples might be too project-specific\n2. Asks for clarification when patterns seem narrow\n3. Correctly identifies the root cause (not just symptoms)\n4. Provides generic rules that work across project types\n5. Shows how the pattern applies in multiple domains\n6. Gives prompt templates with placeholders, not just specific examples\n7. Suggests configuration changes that enforce better behavior\n8. Teaches principles that apply broadly, not just to one case"}]},"tool_response":{"filePath":"/Users/yabo/Documents/Code/phone-to-laptop/tests/verify_analyze_command.md","edits":[{"old_string":"#### Test Case 1: Python Test Auditor Issue\n```bash\n# In Claude Code session:\n/analyze-interaction tests/sample_bad_interaction.txt\n```\n\n**Expected Output Should Include:**\n\n🔍 **What Went Wrong**: Agent created test_commands_real.py instead of updating test_commands.py\n\n🎯 **Why It Happened**: \n- Primary: No explicit rule against creating file versions\n- Contributing: Agent name implied creating \"real\" tests as separate entity\n\n🛠️ **How to Fix It**:\n```xml\n<rule id=\"R003\" importance=\"critical\">\nNEVER create file versions (index_new.py, script_v2.js, test_real.py)\nYOU MUST edit original files directly\nWhen asked to improve tests, UPDATE existing test files\n</rule>\n```\n\n**Better Prompt Examples**:\n```\n✅ \"Update tests/test_commands.py to replace mocks with real service calls\"\n```\n\n**Subagent Configuration**:\n```yaml\nname: python-test-auditor\ndescription: Reviews and UPDATES EXISTING test files to ensure meaningful testing\ntools: Read, Edit, MultiEdit, Grep\n```","new_string":"#### Test Case 1: File Duplication Pattern\n```bash\n# In Claude Code session:\n/analyze-interaction tests/sample_bad_interaction.txt\n```\n\n**Expected Output Should Include:**\n\n⚠️ **Specificity Check**: The example appears to involve test files. Should this solution be generic or specific to testing?\n\n🔍 **What Went Wrong**: Agent created new file with suffix instead of updating existing file\n\n🎯 **Why It Happened**: \n- Primary: No explicit rule against creating file versions\n- Contributing: Ambiguous instruction about \"improving\" vs \"updating\"\n\n🛠️ **How to Fix It**:\n```xml\n<rule id=\"R###\" importance=\"critical\">\nNEVER create file versions with suffixes (_new, _v2, _improved, _real, etc.)\nYOU MUST edit original files directly\nExamples: test.py not test_v2.py, index.js not index_new.js, config.yaml not config_updated.yaml\n</rule>\n```\n\n**Better Prompt Examples (Generic)**:\n```\n❌ AVOID: \"Improve the [files]\"\n✅ BETTER: \"Update [specific_file] to [specific_change]\"\n\nDomain Examples:\n- Web: \"Update components/Button.tsx to use new design system\"\n- API: \"Update routes/auth.py to add rate limiting\"\n- Tests: \"Update test_module.py to replace mocks with real calls\"\n```","replace_all":false},{"old_string":"#### Test Case 2: Description Only\n```bash\n/analyze-interaction Agent kept creating new files even after I said to edit existing ones\n```\n\nShould analyze the pattern and suggest prevention strategies.","new_string":"#### Test Case 2: Description Only\n```bash\n/analyze-interaction Agent kept creating new files even after I said to edit existing ones\n```\n\n**Expected Output Should Include:**\n- Recognition that this is a generic file management issue\n- Request for clarification: \"What types of files? In what context?\"\n- Generic rule that applies to all file types\n- Multiple examples from different domains","replace_all":false},{"old_string":"## Success Criteria\nThe command successfully helps when it:\n1. Correctly identifies the root cause (not just symptoms)\n2. Provides a rule that would have prevented the issue\n3. Gives specific prompt language that avoids ambiguity\n4. Suggests configuration changes that enforce better behavior\n5. Teaches a principle that applies to similar situations","new_string":"## Success Criteria\nThe command successfully helps when it:\n1. Detects when examples might be too project-specific\n2. Asks for clarification when patterns seem narrow\n3. Correctly identifies the root cause (not just symptoms)\n4. Provides generic rules that work across project types\n5. Shows how the pattern applies in multiple domains\n6. Gives prompt templates with placeholders, not just specific examples\n7. Suggests configuration changes that enforce better behavior\n8. Teaches principles that apply broadly, not just to one case","replace_all":false}],"originalFileContents":"# How to Test /analyze-interaction Command\n\n## Testing Strategy (Per R002)\n\n### 1. How Claude Can Test (Automated)\nCannot directly invoke slash commands from tools, but can verify:\n- Command file exists at ~/.claude/commands/analyze-interaction.md\n- Frontmatter is properly formatted YAML\n- Command will be recognized by Claude Code\n\n### 2. How Human Can Test (Manual)\n\n#### Test Case 1: Python Test Auditor Issue\n```bash\n# In Claude Code session:\n/analyze-interaction tests/sample_bad_interaction.txt\n```\n\n**Expected Output Should Include:**\n\n🔍 **What Went Wrong**: Agent created test_commands_real.py instead of updating test_commands.py\n\n🎯 **Why It Happened**: \n- Primary: No explicit rule against creating file versions\n- Contributing: Agent name implied creating \"real\" tests as separate entity\n\n🛠️ **How to Fix It**:\n```xml\n<rule id=\"R003\" importance=\"critical\">\nNEVER create file versions (index_new.py, script_v2.js, test_real.py)\nYOU MUST edit original files directly\nWhen asked to improve tests, UPDATE existing test files\n</rule>\n```\n\n**Better Prompt Examples**:\n```\n✅ \"Update tests/test_commands.py to replace mocks with real service calls\"\n```\n\n**Subagent Configuration**:\n```yaml\nname: python-test-auditor\ndescription: Reviews and UPDATES EXISTING test files to ensure meaningful testing\ntools: Read, Edit, MultiEdit, Grep\n```\n\n#### Test Case 2: Description Only\n```bash\n/analyze-interaction Agent kept creating new files even after I said to edit existing ones\n```\n\nShould analyze the pattern and suggest prevention strategies.\n\n#### Test Case 3: Real Conversation Log\n```bash\n# If you have an actual .jsonl conversation file:\n/analyze-interaction ~/.claude/projects/[project]/[session].jsonl\n```\n\n## Verification Checklist\n- [ ] Command appears in `/help` list showing \"(user)\"\n- [ ] Accepts file paths (.txt, .log, .json, .jsonl)\n- [ ] Accepts text descriptions\n- [ ] Identifies specific anti-patterns (file duplication, mock overuse, etc.)\n- [ ] Provides CLAUDE.md rule in proper XML format\n- [ ] Shows before/after prompt examples with ❌ and ✅\n- [ ] Suggests subagent configuration if applicable\n- [ ] Includes actionable implementation checklist\n- [ ] References Claude Code documentation patterns\n\n## Success Criteria\nThe command successfully helps when it:\n1. Correctly identifies the root cause (not just symptoms)\n2. Provides a rule that would have prevented the issue\n3. Gives specific prompt language that avoids ambiguity\n4. Suggests configuration changes that enforce better behavior\n5. Teaches a principle that applies to similar situations","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":10,"oldLines":7,"newStart":10,"newLines":7,"lines":[" "," ### 2. How Human Can Test (Manual)"," ","-#### Test Case 1: Python Test Auditor Issue","+#### Test Case 1: File Duplication Pattern"," ```bash"," # In Claude Code session:"," /analyze-interaction tests/sample_bad_interaction.txt"]},{"oldStart":18,"oldLines":31,"newStart":18,"newLines":32,"lines":[" "," **Expected Output Should Include:**"," ","-🔍 **What Went Wrong**: Agent created test_commands_real.py instead of updating test_commands.py","+⚠️ **Specificity Check**: The example appears to involve test files. Should this solution be generic or specific to testing?"," ","+🔍 **What Went Wrong**: Agent created new file with suffix instead of updating existing file","+"," 🎯 **Why It Happened**: "," - Primary: No explicit rule against creating file versions","-- Contributing: Agent name implied creating \"real\" tests as separate entity","+- Contributing: Ambiguous instruction about \"improving\" vs \"updating\""," "," 🛠️ **How to Fix It**:"," ```xml"