gs, and agents not following conventions.\n\n5. **From Hooks documentation**: Hooks can analyze tool usage patterns and provide feedback to Claude about what went wrong.\n \nI'll refine the approach by creating a more targeted diagnostic tool. The command needs strategic enhancements to capture nuanced interaction problems, focusing on precise detection of agent misalignments and workflow inefficiencies. I'll develop a multi-layered analysis framework that can systematically break down complex interaction challenges, providing granular insights into potential improvements.\n\nKey focus areas will include:\n- Detecting subtle pattern deviations\n- Mapping unintended agent behaviors\n- Generating contextually relevant optimization strategies\n- Providing actionable, implementable recommendations",
